description: The Gwangju Joseon Official Kiln Museum is located in Gwangju, Gyeonggi-do, where the official kiln operated by the royal family during the Joseon Dynasty was set up and operated for more than 400 years. Study Korean white porcelain, excavate Korean official kiln ruins, academic research, traditional pottery culture education and other Korean traditional pottery.
